g.title: 1678 Manticore Engraving, by Joannes Johnstonus
g.desc: From https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Martigora_engraving.jpg : The Manticore, or Martigora was described by Pliny and Aristotle as a creature with the face and ears of a human, with grey eyes and a red body; a tail with a sting like that of a scorpion, and being the size of a lion, and with a lionâ€™s paws, a triple row of teeth and an appetite for human flesh.
